value.0: The toddler crown prince of the Kingdom of Kohlingen is well-dressed and playful. With his big smile and bright blue-green eyes, it's clear he takes after his mother.

A stunning portrait of the late King Gregory Simmons, his intense brown eyes clearly the focal point of the piece. It is a familiar visage to many, capturing him at the peak of his health and influence.

Gregory Simmons served under the late Justicar Cystana L'saenirais, taking the position of the sixth Justicar of Kohlingen after the death of his predecessor. He went on to become the first king of the Kingdom of Kohlingen after the founding of Fort Cystana and the recovery of the fallen Holy City. He gave his life to secure the protection of the people of Kohlingen in 1390 DR.

A striking portrait of the late Justicar Cystana L'saenirais, after whom the capital of the Kingdom of Kohlingen was named. This portrait draws attention to the fierce determination and nobility for which she was known.

Lady Cystana was the fifth Justicar of the Holy City of Kohlingen and a Red Falconer of the Red Knight. She was the first woman to be chosen and confirmed for the position, the first non-paladin, and the first to hold a patron not among the Lords of the Triad. Well-respected by both the Church of the Triad and her people, she gave her life in defense of her home during the Dragonbane War in 1387 DR.
